{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"adb18f3c-b438-4d20-9637-ea253dd6067d","content":"No files found in the working directory — so this is a guidance question rather than a file-editing task. Here's how to do it:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to enable compiled bindings\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the namespace for your ViewModel and set `x:DataType` on the root element:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is the single line: **`x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`**. This tells the XAML compiler to resolve all `{Binding ...}` expressions against `SettingsViewModel` at compile time.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nOnce `x:DataType` is set, **misspelled or missing properties become build errors**, not silent runtime failures. To maximize coverage:\n\n**a) Enable warnings-as-errors for bindings in your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n    <!-- Optionally treat all warnings as errors: -->\n    <TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**b) Example error you'll now see:**\n\nIf you typo `{Binding Themee}`, the build fails with:\n\n```\nerror XC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Opting out for specific bindings\n\nIf a binding must stay dynamic (e.g., binding to a different runtime type), use `x:DataType=\"\"` locally:\n\n```xml\n<Label x:DataType=\"\" Text=\"{Binding SomeDynamicProp}\" />\n```\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` to the `<ContentPage>` root → all `{Binding}` paths are validated at compile time → typos and type mismatches become build errors instead of silent failures.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d4887fbd-43e9-4e10-bf3e-454f9cc157e8","outputTokens":769},"id":"2543e9b4-fc96-4869-b766-86c67c405362","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:00:30.216Z","parentId":"7d277c39-02f6-492f-8852-9b752ba7d478"}
